general.headline: CEO @ProStarSoftware: ERP Integration, Secure Payments, Digital Transformation
general.description:
Delivering enterprise software solutions and fit-to-business enhancements to provide a better fit between business's needs and the business's systems. Forward-facing technology from ProStar Software complements, adapts and integrates enterprise business systems and their users, on any device. Business policies automatically enforced; complex business activities automatically coordinated. Systems follow the business's rules, not the other way around. Your system, your way.

35+ years of leading-edge management, executive and consulting experience delivering return on investment and enabling growth. Improved profitability for vertical industries including medical, electronics, capital equipment, automotive and consumer goods.

ProStar Software provides customizations and integrations, including mobile, with no changes to your current systems' source code or db schema. Products include the TailorPro non-invasive customization development platform, Mobile Enterprise Integration and Credit Card Integration.

Specialties: 
- Producing rapid ROI (weeks-months) by enabling bona fide business requirements into the business system.
- Providing value-focused ERP, BPM, Integration and Mobile solutions to complement any version of QAD Enterprise Applications.
- Ethical business practices and high attention to customer satisfaction.

jobs.description:
Organizational and technical oversight, market development, product vision. 

ProStar's products: 
Credit Card Integration + Enhanced Compliance (CCI+EC) provides PCI DSS compliant credit card processing integrated with OpenEdge (Progress) applications like QAD. 

The TailorPro logic and rules engine, event processor and SDK provides the capability for companies to achieve the fit they need between their unique business requirements and their business system with no change to the base application's source code or the production database schema.
Responsible for IT, Operations and Distribution
